news.title: Government allows 5% increase in project costs: Gujarat contractors’ association
news.para: In the wake of surging prices of steel, cement, gravel, bricks and other construction materials, the association members had been lobbying for revision of construction contracts to raise prices.

news.title: RLDA invites bid for residential development near Howrah railway station
news.para: For this site a built-up area of approximately 20925 square meters is proposed with Floor Space Index (FSI) of 2.25 for the complete plot size.

news.title: After Telangana CM's promise, land rates set to soar in GO 111 villages
news.para: The present values in these areas range from Rs 5 crore to Rs 10 crore per acre and are likely to double once the GO is scrapped.

news.title: Rajasthan housing minister says 2.28 lakh lease deeds issued during Shahar campaign
news.para: He said, 10,62,790 applications for building permission, name transfer, subdivision, reconstitution, lease and others have been disposed of in the camps.

news.title: Irregularities found in PMAY-G in Odisha: Rural minister
news.para: In a written reply to the Rajya Sabha, the Union minister on Wednesday said multiple representations, including one from MPs from the state have been received by the ministry regarding the irregularities in the execution of PMAY-G in Odisha.

news.title: Give details of properties auctioned in year: Chandigarh administration
news.para: The UT is planning to finalise auction plan of unsold commercial and industrial properties and nursing home sites on freehold basis.

news.title: NGO urge Nagpur collector to rehabilitate slum-dwellers before evicting them
news.para: TOI on March 14 reported about collector office serving demolition notices to over 30 houses situated along the nullah at Mariam Nagar in Civil Lines.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seeks Rs 325 crore in property tax dues
news.para: The AMC has to collect Rs 72 crore for properties belonging to Calico Mills Ltd, and Rs 15 crore from Western Railway for properties including Kalupur railway station, its pay and park facilities as well as the divisional railway manager’s office building.

news.title: CBI arrests professor who certified Chintels Paradiso in bribery case
news.para: Moin had allegedly given the structural safety certificate to the Chintels Paradiso apartment in Gurugram, part of which collapsed last month killing two women. His arrest, however, was not connected to the house collapse.

news.title: Gera Developments to invest Rs 500 crore in Pimpri Chinchwad project
news.para: The firm said it was investing around Rs 540 crore into the project, which is due to be completed by December 2025.

news.title: Gurugram: Maria Sharapova & Michael Schumacher booked for fraud
news.para: Earlier, she had filed a complaint in a Gurugram court against M/S Realtech Development and Infrastructure (INDIA) Pvt. Ltd, other developers, Sharapova and Schumacher for duping her of around Rs 80 lakh.

news.title: DLF expects its rental income to increase more than Rs 1,500 crore over the next four years
news.para: ​​DCCDL has rent-yielding commercial assets, both offices and retail properties, of about 35 million sq ft, the majority of which are in Delhi-National Capital Region. With the office segment’s recovery riding on the economic recovery, the segment is witnessing a steady uptake, especially from international and domestic IT companies.

news.title: Noida: Two builders' bank accounts frozen over pending recovery dues
news.para: Recovery certificates are orders issued by Rera, asking builders to clear dues of buyers in case of failure to deliver projects within the stipulated deadline.

news.title: HC tells Mumbai civic body to transfer Worli plot title to Century Textiles
news.para: The listed textiles-to-realty company had approached the city corporation in March 2014, seeking to execute a formal deed of conveyance for the land, which houses a residential colony of its employees. It moved the high court in December 2016, after the authorities did not respond to its application and several letters seeking transfer of the land title.

news.title: Brookfield Asset to buy IL&FS headquarter for Rs 1,100 crore
news.para: People with direct knowledge of the development said Brookfield made the highest offer for the 10-storied property that most accurately captures the pronounced northward shift in Mumbai's financial nerve centre, away from Nariman Point on the southern tip of the metropolis.
